  <summary date="2011-01-31T16:33:30Z" status="Introduced in House">Constitutional Amendment - Prohibits outlays for a fiscal year (except those for repayment of debt principal) from exceeding one-fifth of economic output of the United States, unless two-thirds of each chamber provide for a specific increase of outlays above this amount.

 Authorizes waivers of these provisions when a declaration of war is in effect.</summary>
